### **12. INTERACTIVE DRAG MECHANICS**

**Pointer Down:** (lines 340-371)

```javascript
const handleStarPointerDown = useCallback((postId, screenX, screenY) => {
    const body = bodiesRef.current.get(postId);
    if (!body) return;

    isStarDragging.current = true;

    // Wake up if sleeping
    if (body.isSleeping) {
        Body.set(body, 'isSleeping', false);
    }

    // Convert screen coords → world coords (accounting for camera/zoom)
    const worldPos = screenToWorld(screenX, screenY, cameraRef.current, zoomRef.current, stageSizeRef.current);

    // Create temporary constraint pinning body to cursor
    dragPointRef.current = { x: worldPos.x, y: worldPos.y };
    dragBodyRef.current = body;

    const constraint = Constraint.create({
        bodyA: body,
        pointB: dragPointRef.current,    // Fixed world point (NOT body)
        length: 0,
        stiffness: 0.1,                   // Stiff constraint
        damping: 0.05,
    });

    World.add(engine.world, constraint);
    dragConstraintRef.current = constraint;
});
```

**Pointer Move:** (lines 373-384)

```javascript
const handlePointerMove = useCallback((screenX, screenY) => {
    if (!isStarDragging.current || !dragConstraintRef.current) return;

    const worldPos = screenToWorld(screenX, screenY, cameraRef.current, zoomRef.current, stageSizeRef.current);

